<h1>Unit 4, Lesson 1: Body Planes and Directions</h1> 




<h2>1-General Body Plane Information (Question=3)</h2> 




<p>What is a body plane?</p> 




<p><b>A directional term that describes a section of the body</b></p> 




<p>A way to describe a body part in relation to a second body 


part</p> 




<p>A method of abbreviation for body organs</p> 




<p>The position in which a patient must lie</p> 




<p> </p> 




<p>The correct anatomical position is the body upright and 


facing with:</p> 




<p><b>The arms down at the sides and palms facing forward</b></p> 




<p>The arms down at the sides and palms facing backward</p> 




<p>The arms raised the sides and palms facing forward</p> 




<p>The arms raised at the sides and palms facing backward</p> 




<p> </p> 




<p>When in the correct anatomical position, the palms of the 


hand are facing:</p> 




<p><b>Forward</b></p> 




<p>Backward</p> 




<p>In toward the body</p> 




<p>Out away from the body</p> 




<p> </p>
